      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey i am trying to buy my first house and i keep hearing the word escrow. can u explain what that actually is and what happens to my earnest money during the process?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Escrow, a process that's quite familiar to many a homebuyer, is a crucial step in the homebuying process. It's a trust account that holds funds for you and the seller until certain conditions are met, such as the sale being finalized and the property being transferred to your name. Think of it like a temporary safekeeping of your earnest money, ensuring that both parties fulfill their obligations. The escrow agent acts as a neutral third party, holding the funds until the sale is complete, at which point they're disbursed accordingly. This protects both you and the seller, preventing any disputes or misunderstandings.",
